cs.RO, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.AI, cs.CG 

This paper deals with a robotics problem of searching for a line on a plane, which falls under the category of robotics and control (cs.RO). The problem involves algorithms and data structures for coordinating the movements of multiple robots, which could also be classified under data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses competitive ratios and lower bounds, which are concepts commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
